# Practical 1 — Windows System Monitoring

## Overview

This practical focuses on real-time Windows system monitoring using built-in monitoring and troubleshooting tools.

The objective of this lab is to understand how Windows manages:
- CPU resources
- Memory utilization
- Disk activity
- Running processes
- Resource consumption
- System performance monitoring

This practical simulates basic enterprise-level troubleshooting scenarios commonly performed by:
- IT Support Engineers
- SOC Analysts
- System Administrators
- Helpdesk Engineers
- Cybersecurity Professionals

