# Important Notes

## 1. Task Manager is a Real Troubleshooting Tool

Task Manager is not only used to close applications.

Enterprise administrators and SOC analysts use it to:
- identify abnormal resource usage
- monitor system performance
- investigate suspicious activity
- troubleshoot slow systems

---

## 2. High CPU Usage May Indicate

- heavy workloads
- unstable applications
- malware activity
- background scanning
- update processes

---

## 3. High Memory Usage Can Cause

- application lag
- browser slowdown
- reduced responsiveness
- system freezing

---

## 4. Disk Bottlenecks Are Common

High disk usage with slow response time may indicate:
- antivirus scanning
- indexing
- Windows updates
- storage issues
- excessive background activity

---

# Secret Tips & Practical Insights

## Tip 1 — Sort Processes by Resource Usage

Always sort:
- CPU
- Memory
- Disk

to quickly identify problematic applications.

---

## Tip 2 — Use Resource Monitor for Deep Analysis

Resource Monitor provides:
- file-level operations
- handle monitoring
- detailed disk activity
- process filtering

which is extremely useful during advanced troubleshooting.

---

## Tip 3 — Malware Often Shows Resource Abnormalities

Suspicious malware may:
- consume abnormal CPU
- generate unusual disk activity
- create unknown processes
- use excessive memory

Monitoring tools help identify such anomalies.

---

## Tip 4 — Generate Real Activity During Practice

To better understand monitoring:
- open multiple browser tabs
- run scans
- copy large files
- observe real-time graph changes

This improves practical understanding.
